inn1.comm: good length ball to begin the innings. Tamim comes forward and defends it to the off side
fuller on the middle and off. Tamim comes forward and turns it to the leg side
comes forward and turns it to the leg side
outside the off stump and left all alone
comes forward and turns it to the leg side and gets a single for himself
good length ball on the off stump. Shamsur comes forward and defends it solidly.
oversteps and on the off stump. Tamim comes forward and defends it. There is a roar for the free hit to follow
short ball outside the off stump. Tamim looks to cut it over point and the bounce beats him
cuts it to point
good length ball on the off stump. Tamim comes forward and defends it to the off side
good length ball outside the off stump. Tamim defends it to point
good length ball on the off stump and moving away a touch. Tamim moves across and defends it to the off side
half-volley outside the off stump. Tamim comes forward and smashes it past mid-off for a boundary
good length ball outside the off stump. He looks to defend it and is beaten by the movement
comes forward and defends it to off side
good length delivery. Shaping in and moves away after pitching. Predictably, the batsman was squared-up but didn't get any edge
comes forward and defends it to the midwicket fielder
outside off and left alone
fuller ball on the off stump. Shamsur comes forward and punches it back to the bowler
outside the off stump and left alone by Tamim
good length ball, rising after pitching. Tamim moves across and shoulders arms
Good length ball on the off stump. Tamim defends it to mid-on
good length ball outside the off stump. Tamim moves across and opens the face of the bat to run it down to third-man for a boundary
Tamim looks like he had a brainfreeze. For some reason he steps out and wants to loft it over midwicket. Ball was short and rising by the time he played it. Lucky to be still around
squares him up with an away moving delivery
good length ball outside the off stump. Shamsur pushes it to cover
comes forward and pushes it to the leg side for a single
outside the off stump and left all alone by the batsman
fuller ball outside the off stump. Tamim leans forward and drives it to cover
this time he splits the gap at cover as he drives past the two fielders there for a boundary
reaches out for the delivery outside the off stump and gets an outside edge to third-man for a single
outside the off stump and left alone
short ball outside the off stump. Tamim skips down the track and smashes it past covers for a boundary. Now to see what he does the next delivery
comes down the track and punches it to cover
comes forward and defends it to point
fuller ball on the off stump. Shamsur drives it to mid-off
good length ball outside the off stump. Shamsur comes forward and punches it to cover
fuller ball outside the off stump. Shamsur drives it to mid-off
flicks it to deep mid wicket and gets a couple
comes forward and turns it to leg side for a single
good length ball and coming in after pitching. Shamsur looks to defend it and is beaten by the inward movement
comes forward and defends it to the off side
moves across and whips it. He gets an inside edge onto the pad and wants a single. Tamim runs and refuses it at the last moment. A wayward throw from the fielder saves him
comes forward and creams a gorgeous drive, but the fielding at cover is even more exceptional as he stops what would've been a certain boundary
comes forward and defends it back to the bowler
fuller ball on the off stump. Tamim jumps down the track and lofts it high over long-off for a huge six. What a shot!
comes forward and pushes it back to the bowler
short ball on the off stump. Tamim defends it by going up on his toes
comes forward and plays it with soft hands to the leg side
off the pads to the fine-leg boundary. Runs, in any form, are welcome for Bangladesh
comes forward and drives it to cover
the pressure of dot balls seems to be getting to Shamsur as he comes down the track and plays an ugly slog. He doesn't connect
comes forward and defends it back onto the pitch
comes forward and pushes a fuller ball to the leg side
comes forward and defends it back to the bowler
pushes it to the leg side
comes forward and defends it back to the bowler
pushes it to midwicket for a single
wide down the leg side
on the leg stump line. Shamsur turns it to short fine-leg for a single
steers it to short third-man for a single
bounces from a good length. Tamim is surprised and fends it off at the last moment
comes forward and drives it to mid-off for a single
comes forward and turns it to square-leg for a single
drives it to sweeper cover for a single
moves back and across and turns it to square-leg for a single
pushes it to leg side
comes forward and defends it back to the bowler
starts off with a yorker and Shamsur does well to get clamp the bat down on it
comes forward and pushes it to the off side
defends it to cover
fuller ball on the off stump. Shamsur drives it to the point
slower ball on the middle stump. Shamsur looks to pull it away and is hit on the arm
short ball on the off stump. Shamsur pulls it to deep mid wicket for a single
fuller ball on the off stump. Shamsur looks to sweep it and misses. There is a huge appeal, but the umpire is unmoved as it would've sailed over
comes forward and slogs it over square-leg for a huge six
and again as he takes this from outside the off stump and lofts it  over square-leg for another six
defends it back to the bowler
good length ball outside the off stump. Tamim looks to open the face and run it down to third-man. The away movement beats him
square-drives it to deep point for a single
comes down the track and drives it to cover
steers it to third-man for a single
drives it to sweeper cover for a single
comes forward and turns it to midwicket
turns it to deep midwicket for a single
drives it to cover for a single
comes down the track in an attempt to get his third six. He misses and Latham collects the ball and has enough time to whip the bails off
comes forward and steers it to short third-man
good length ball outside the off stump. Mominul looks to drive it and is beaten
pushes it to the leg side and gets off the mark with a single
stands tall and drives it to deep point for a couple
comes forward and whips it to short third-man
drives it to long-on for a single
fuller ball outside the off stump. He moves across and whips it to midwicket
turns it to the leg side for a single
comes forward and drives it to point
short ball outside the off stump. Mominul guides it past vacant slip region for a boundary
outside the off stump and left alone by Mominul
comes forward and turns it to deep midwicket for a couple
makes room and smashes it past point for a boundary
off the pad to the onside.
defended square of the wicket on the off side.
driven firmly down the ground to the long on fence, presents the full face off the bat.
gets it down to deep backward square leg.
punches square of the wicket to point.
works it through the vacant midwicket for a single.
pushes to the off side.
comes down the track and pads it away.
cut to the sweeper on the off side.
dabs it down to third man for a single.
short and wide, cut in the air over the slip and down to third man fence.
defended square of the wicket on the off side.
full delivery driven to the left of mid-on to the fence for a boundary.
bit wide outside the off stump.
mistimes it through midwicket for a single.
arm ball strikes the pad, loud appeal, inside edge.
short ball pulled to deep midwicket.
punches to point.
plays it behind the wicket on the onside for a quick single.
once again an inside edge onto the pads.
driven down the ground to long off.
good length ball outside the off stump. He makes room and slices it to point
fuller ball outside the off stump. Mominul comes forward and pushes it to point
fuller ball on the middle stump. Mominul comes forward and drives it back to the bowler
that's a wicket! Short and slower ball on the off stump. Mominul is early into the pull shot and doesn't get enough bat on it as he ends up holing out to Nathan McCullum at deep mid wicket
comes forward and pushes it to point
short on the leg stump. Tamim leaps and tucks it to midwicket for a single
comes forward and punches it to cover and sets off for a quick single
strays down the leg side line. Rahim paddles it to short fine-leg for a single
short ball outside the off stump. Tamim cuts and wants a single. Perhaps he wants the half-century badly as he sets off for a non existent single and gets back in time
comes forward and pushes it back to the bowler
short ball on the leg stump. Tamim pushes it to midwicket. Rahim understands him well as he shouts a loud no before the ball got to the fielder
short ball on the off stump. Rahim drives it to point off the back foot
fuller and slower outside the off stump. Rahim comes forward and defends it to cover
yorker on the off stump. Rahim stays fixed to crease and digs it out
short ball on the off stump. Rahim pulls and doesn't connect as it ends up to the right of the pitch. Tamim wants a single and gets back in time. Again! What's with his running?
short ball outside the off stump. Rahim looks to cut it and is beaten
short ball outside the off stump. Rahim cuts it to point and the dive by the fielder saves a boundary
comes forward and pushes it to cover
settles the nerves down with a push to mid-off for a single. Gets to his half-century and there is a lot of work ahead of him in this innings
defends it to the off side
fuller ball on the off stump. How many times have we seen Rahim going down on one knee and slogging it over deep square-leg. That's a brilliant shot
comes forward and pushes it to mid-on for a single
fuller ball outside the off stump. Tamim drives and the fielder at silly mid-off pulls off a good stop
comes forward and drives it to sweeper cover for a single
fuller ball on the off stump. Tamim comes down the track and looks to loft it away. Doesn't cover the line and doesn't cover the length. Just a wild swing and he misses
comes down the track and pulls again! This time he connects and gets a couple
fuller ball on the off stump. Tamim flicks it to wide mid-on for a single
short and slower on the leg stump. Rahim turns it to fine-leg for a single
comes down the track and chips it to mid-on for a single
good length ball outside the off stump. Tamim runs it to third-man for a single
drives it to deep point and takes a couple
turns it to square-leg for a single
good length ball outside the off stump. Tamim steers it to third-man where good fielding by Anderson limits him to a couple
comes down the track and looks to loft it away. He is beaten by the away movement
comes forward and pushes it to point
comes forward and runs it to short third-man for a single
comes forward and turns it to square-leg for a single

Tamim's frustration gets the better of him! Good length ball outside the off stump. Tamim jumps down the track and looks to loft it away. This time he gets an inside edge and see's the stumps rearranged. That's poor batting from Tamim- he allowed the frustration of not scoring boundaries get to him and it ultimately led to his dismissal
drives it to long-off for a single. Doesn't take as much time as in the first ODI to get off the mark
comes forward and guides it to short third-man
short ball outside the off stump. Naeem stands tall and cuts it over point for a boundary. Good shot.
drives it to sweeper cover for a single
fuller ball outside the off stump. Rahim square-drives it to deep point for a single
fuller ball outside the off stump. Naeem lofts it to sweeper cover for a single
short ball outside the off stump. Rahim cuts it powerfully. The fielder at point takes the pace off the ball and deflects it to sweeper cover and saves three runs for his team
comes forward and defends a slower ball back to the bowler
comes forward and turns it to mid wicket for a single
comes forward and drives it to cover
short ball outside the off stump. Naeem rocks back and cuts it to deep point for a single
steers it to short third-man for a single
comes forward and tries to repeat the stroke of his captain, but the fielder is quicker to the ball this time
turns it to deep square-leg for a single
looks to cut and is beaten
short ball outside the off stump. Naeem looks to cut it and is beaten again
slower ball outside the off stump. Naeem punches it back to the bowler
comes forward and drives it to mid-off
short and a slow off-cutter. Naeem Islam is beaten by the lack of pace and looks back at his captain
good length ball outside the off stump. Naeem cuts it to point and that's a maiden for Southee
short ball on the off stump. Rahim pulls it to deep mid wicket for a single
good length ball on the off stump. Naeem looks to slice it and is beaten. Crowd voices its agitation by shouting at him
fuller ball on the off stump. Naeem obliges the crowd by stepping out and lofting it over long-on for a six
pulls it to square-leg for a single
goes inside-out over mid-off for a boundary
short ball on the off stump. Rahim pulls it to deep square-leg for a single
wide down the leg side
slower ball outside the off stump. Rahim looks to steer it at the last moment and misses. He is angry with himself for not being able to get bat on the ball
fuller ball on the off stump. Rahim slog sweeps it over cow corner for a six
and that's the wicket! Rahim skips down the track and looks to loft it away. He gets an outside edge that Latham takes by just moving his hands to the right
comes forward and pushes it to cover
comes forward and pushes it back to the batsman
short ball on the off stump. Nasir cuts and gets a couple for himself

Naeem decides to chase a short ball on the leg stump line. He had no option left as he had shuffled across before the bowler could bowl. He only manages to get some glove on it and has to depart. Bangladesh's innings is coming undone in the powerplay overs
comes forward and drives it to cover
steers it to point
good length ball on the off stump. Mahmudullah defends it back onto the pitch
comes forward and pushes it to mid-on for a single
comes forward and punches it to mid-off for a single
short ball outside the off stump. He gets behind the line of the delivery and defends it

that's the third wicket in the batting powerplay! Fuller ball outside the off stump. Nasir lofts it and doesn't get enough power on the stroke to propel it over long-off. McCullum manning the long-off area runs back a few steps and takes an easy catch
comes forward and turns it to square-leg for a single
short ball on the middle stump. Gazi takes his eyes off the ball and ducks under it
comes forward and pushes it to square-leg for a single
comes forward and defends a length ball back to the bowler

comes forward and defends it to point. The non-striker and the fielder at point are quicker to respond than the batsman. Gazi responds late and only a poor flick by the fielder at point saves him from making the trudge back to the pavilion
defends it to cover
steers it to short third-man for a single
turns it to midwicket for a single
forces it to mid wicket for a single
and there's a gift- a free hit as Mills oversteps and the crowd shout out their approval
short ball and Gazi cashes on the free hit as he pulls it to deep midwicket for a boundary
wide down the leg side. Every run being cheered for by the crowd
short of a good length delivery. The ball doesn't rise as expected because Mahmudullah ducked but the ball just went over him
short ball and Mahmudullah pulls it to deep mid wicket for his first boundary
comes forward and turns it to square-leg for a single
comes forward and steers it to third-man for a single

looks to cut it and gets a bottom edge to the keeper
comes forward and pushes it to mid-on for a single
fuller ball outside the off stump. Mahmudullah pushes it to sweeper cover and sets off for a single
short ball on the off stump. Gazi pulls it to wide mid-on for a single
good length ball on the off stump and coming in. Gazi slogs it across the line and gets it to travel the distance.
comes forward and punches it to cover
wide as it was pitched short and sails over the head of the batsman
fuller ball on the off stump. Gazi turns it to square-leg for a single
off the inside edge to fine-leg for a single
short ball outside the off stump. Gazi steers it to short third-man for a single
comes forward and drives it to mid-on for a single
short ball outside the off stump. Gazi looks to cut it and is beaten
steers it to  third-man for a single
comes forward and drives it to long-on for a single
pushes it to point and sets off for a quick single
comes forward and punches it to mid-on for a single
fuller ball on the leg stump. Mahmudullah turns it to deep square-leg for a single
makes room and looks to cut it. Devcich takes the catch but the ball pops out as he hits the ground. He ran back from cover and had to dive to take the catch. Gazi gets a single for the effort
turns it to square-leg for a single
short ball. Mahmudullah, for some reason, charges down the track and looks to pull it. All he gets is a top edge and that's an easy offering for the bowler
comes forward and upper cuts it to third-man for boundary. He opened the face of the bat at the last moment
comes forward and defends it to cover
short ball on the off stump. Mashrafe looks to pull it and gets an under edge that trickles back to the bowler
comes forward and pushes it to square-leg for a single
that's unfortunate for Latham as the ball bounces just before him and runs away for four byes. Bangladesh have stuck in there and are inching towards what looks a good total
comes forward and ducks under the bouncer
short ball. Gazi makes room and looks to cut it. He does, but straight into the hands of the fielder at  point
good length ball outside the off stump. Rubel looks to defend it and is beaten. Latham fumbles with the take and they run across for a bye
full-toss on the leg stump. Razzak turns it to deep square-leg for a couple

chips it to mid-off and sets off for a single
comes forward and flicks it to deep square-leg for a single
looks to pull and is beaten by the bounce
steps out and pulls it to deep mid wicket for a single
and Bangladesh can't play out the fifty overs as Rubel is beaten all ends up by the yorker.

on the leg stump. Taylor turns it to square-leg and for a moment wants the second. Latham, though, is quicker than he expects him to be and is half way down the pitch. Rahim collects the throw and whips the bails off before Latham can get back to the crease. Bangladesh's match to lose from here on
